    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require airlines to stop school holiday price hikes if they receive bail out",
        "additional_details": "There is a direct correlation between school attendance and results, and families should be able to enjoy a summer or Easter holiday without having to pay hugely inflated prices.",
        "background": "If the Government uses taxpayer money to bail out airlines then this should be conditional on the airlines agreeing to end price rises during school holidays, which affect families the most.",
